.Dd May 25, 2026
.Dt XTC_STRERROR 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xtc_strerror
.Nd return a stable English description of an xtc error code
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In xtc.h
.Ft const char *
.Fn xtc_strerror "int xtc_err"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn xtc_strerror
function returns a stable English description of the xtc error code
.Fa xtc_err .
.Pp
Recognised values are
.Dv XTC_OK
and the
.Dv XTC_E_*
codes declared in
.In xtc.h .
For any code outside the recognised set the function returns the
string
.Dq unknown ;
it never returns
.Dv NULL .
.Pp
The returned pointer is to static storage and must not be freed.
The exact text for each known code is part of the API contract for
log-message stability and changes only on a major version bump.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
A non-NULL pointer to a NUL-terminated string.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
#include <stdio.h>
#include <xtc.h>

void log_rc(int rc) {
        if (rc != XTC_OK)
                fprintf(stderr, "xtc error: %s\en", xtc_strerror(rc));
}
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xtc 7 ,
.Xr xtc_version_string 3
.Sh HISTORY
First appeared in xtc 0.0.1.
